# Core Testing Philosophy

## 1. Testing Principle
All tests must validate observable behavior only.

- Tests define WHAT the system does
- Tests must not depend on HOW it is implemented

---

## 2. Test Structure (MANDATORY BDD FORMAT)

All backend and frontend tests MUST follow Given / When / Then structure:

- GIVEN: initial context
- WHEN: action is executed
- THEN: observable outcome

❌ Arrange / Act / Assert (AAA) is STRICTLY FORBIDDEN  
❌ Mixing AAA and BDD is FORBIDDEN  

---

## 3. Behavior Rule

- One test = one behavior
- Tests must describe a single observable outcome
- Do not combine multiple behaviors

---

## 4. Test Isolation Rule

- Each test must be independent
- No shared mutable state
- Tests must be order-independent

---

## 5. Unit vs Integration Tests

### Unit Tests
- Test logic in isolation
- Dependencies must be mocked or stubbed

### Integration Tests
- Validate interaction between layers
- Use real implementations (or in-memory)
- Must NOT use external production systems

---

## 6. Integration Test Placement (MANDATORY)

- Integration tests MUST target the Presentation layer (controllers)
- Each controller MUST have integration coverage
- Skipping controller integration tests is FORBIDDEN

---

## 7. Test File Policy (STRICT)

- New tests MUST be appended to existing test files
- Creating new test files is FORBIDDEN unless explicitly required

---

## 8. Refactor Safety Rule

- Refactoring must not change behavior
- Tests must NOT be modified unless behavior changes